---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Product designer focused on clarity, systems, and thoughtful delivery in complex domains."
>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-content px-6 py-16 md:py-24">
    <header class="max-w-prose">
      <h1 class="font-serif text-3xl md:text-4xl text-stone-900 leading-tight">About me</h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-stone-700">
        I’m a product designer who cares as much about how teams decide as about what ships. Most of my
        recent work supports regulated or high-stakes products where ambiguity, compliance, and user anxiety
        intersect.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="mt-14 max-w-prose space-y-6 text-stone-700 leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        I partner with product and engineering from discovery through delivery: framing problems with
        research, articulating trade-offs for stakeholders, and making interfaces that feel calm without
        hiding complexity.
      </p>
      <p>
        Before moving into product design, I built a foundation in visual and interaction craft; today I
        spend more time on narrative, IA, and design ops—but still go deep in Figma and in the details of
        interaction states and content.
      </p>
      <h2 class="font-serif text-xl text-stone-900 pt-8">How I work</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
        <li>Ground decisions in evidence—interviews, usage data, and quick prototypes.</li>
        <li>Prefer a small set of strong patterns over one-off screens.</li>
        <li>Write for the people who weren’t in the room: clear artifacts and rationale.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
